  "slug": "roast-poussin",
  "title": "Roast Poussin",
  "subtitle": "A young bird buttered under the skin and roasted in 35 minutes, one per person",
  "excerpt": "Poussin are young chickens weighing 400-500g, sold whole and roasted one per person. They cook in 35 minutes at high heat, need very little seasoning, and are a neater and more elegant plate than a carved roast chicken.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British and French roasting practice. Fanny Cradock, The Ambitious Cook (1970s): poussin roasting guide. Jane Grigson, English Food (1974): small bird timing and presentation.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "poussin",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr30du00007gv4n4b5bexn"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " is the most forgiving roast you can cook: a bird so small that from cold oven door to resting board takes under an hour, and the margin for error is wide. Butter under the skin keeps the breast moist; a hot oven of 220°C gives colour quickly enough that the legs cook through before the breast dries.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One bird per person makes serving straightforward. Each diner gets a whole roasted bird, needing no carving at the table. The alternative is to ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "spatchcock",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpatcpjj0000vsv4vuz7yam5"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " them flat, which reduces cooking time by 10 minutes and gives crispier skin all over, but the whole bird is more elegant for a dinner.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
