      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Butter the birds",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C (200°C fan). Pat each bird dry. Ease the skin from the breast by working your fingers from the neck opening down toward the wishbone. Push ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{unsalted-butter}} of butter",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " under the skin, dividing it evenly between the two birds. Season the skin with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{sea-salt-flakes}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{black-pepper}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and rub with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{olive-oil}} of olive oil",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": ". Tuck a sprig of thyme and a slice of lemon inside each cavity, along with a garlic clove if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roast and rest",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set the birds breast-up in the roasting pan, not touching. Roast for 30-35 minutes until the skin is deep golden and the juices run clear when you pierce the thigh. A probe at the thickest part of the leg should read 75°C. Transfer to a warm plate and rest for 10 minutes before serving. The resting is brief; small birds lose heat quickly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a quick pan gravy",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tip off most of the fat from the roasting pan. Add ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{stock-chicken}} of chicken stock",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and scrape up any fond over medium heat. Simmer for 2 minutes, season, and strain into a warm jug.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "rows": [
            {
              "fix": "Check with an oven thermometer. A 5-minute blast at 240°C at the end will colour pale skin quickly without overcooking the flesh.",
              "cause": "Oven was not fully preheated, or butter on the skin surface is preventing browning",
              "symptom": "Skin is pale after 35 minutes"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Return to the oven for 5-minute increments. Always probe rather than relying on time. Cold birds take 5-10 minutes longer.",
              "cause": "Birds were cold from the fridge, or larger than 500 g",
              "symptom": "Juices run pink at 35 minutes"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull birds at 75°C on the probe. Make sure butter covers both breast fillets, not just one side.",
              "cause": "Overcooked or butter did not distribute evenly",
              "symptom": "Breast is dry"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Rest birds at room temperature for 30 minutes before the oven.",
              "cause": "Bird not at room temperature before roasting",
              "symptom": "Legs and breast cooked unevenly"
            }
          ]
        },
        "content": []
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Poussin fell out of fashion in British home cooking but remains a restaurant staple. They are particularly useful for a two-person dinner where a full roast chicken produces more leftovers than the occasion warrants. The cooking method is identical to a standard roast chicken; the scale is simply smaller, and the result is tidier.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
